The '''Trench''',<ref name="X-Wing: Rogue Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Rogue Squadron]]''</ref> unofficially referred to as '''The Pig Trough''', was an anomalous geographic feature on [[Folor]], the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]]. The meandering fissure's near terminus was a [[Kilometer/Legends|klick]] from the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Folor Base]] and then ran several thousand kilometers northeast, then northwest, and continued an even longer distance. The feature was created in a distant time before the [[New Republic era]] when the moon wasn't yet fully cooled and still had active tectonics.<ref name="Wraith S">''[[X-Wing: Wraith Squadron]]''</ref>

==History==
[[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance command]] had originally the fissure the "Trench" as a memorial to the casualties during the trench run of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] against the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]], but it was later instead nicknamed the "pig trough" due to the reputation of [[BTL Y-wing starfighter/Legends|Y-wings]] as "wallowing [[Swine|pigs]]".<ref name="X-Wing: Rogue Squadron" />

New Republic pilots, particularly the [[RZ-1 A-wing interceptor/Legends|A-wing]], [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]], and [[BTL Y-wing starfighter/Legends|Y-wing]] trainees at Folor Base, used the Pig Trough for practice runs. The deep crevice in the moon's surface with narrow, winding sections gave them a challenge in their fast-moving fighter craft. It was designated a gunnery and bombing range, and when other fighter fighters were practicing in the satellite field orbiting Folor, Y-Wing squadrons dropped charges over the canyon.

When [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]] attacked Folor Base in [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]], Republic [[Flight officer/Legends|Flight officers]] [[Kell Tainer]] and [[Hohass Ekwesh]] of [[Wraith Squadron]] and [[Dorset Konnair]] and [[Tetengo Noor]] of [[Blue Squadron (New Republic)|Blue Squadron]] flew up the Pig Trough (unofficially racing their differing fighter craft along the way) to scout out the [[Implacable (Star Destroyer)/Legends|''Implacable'']]. They also managed to draw the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] to their position as a diversion, using their familiarity with piloting the Pig Trough to have a margin of cover as they flew back to their squadrons, running the gauntlet of Trigit's turbolasers.

Wraith and Blue Squadrons were also able to hide in the Pig Trough as they traveled from Folor Base itself to their engagement zone with the ''Implacable''{{'s}} [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE Interceptors]].

